<p><a href="#sdfootnote2anc" name="sdfootnote2sym">2</a> A distinctive example of the controversies that frequently surrounded the filmmaker during his career is offered, for example, by an event from 2010, when Królikiewicz ostentatiously withdrew his film <em>Kern</em> (2009) from the New Horizons Festival in order to protest against the resignation of the Gutek Film distribution company, run by the festival’s director Roman Gutek, from the distribution of Ewa Stankiewicz’s film <em>Don’t Leave Me</em><em> </em>(2009). Gutek’s decision was motivated by heated debates after the screening of the documentary <em>Solidary 2010 </em>(2010), co-created by Stankiewicz, which depicted the national mourning after the presidential plane crash near Smolensk, and was perceived by liberal milieus as a piece of right-wing political propaganda.</p>
