<p><a href="#sdfootnote16anc" name="sdfootnote16sym">16</a> “I think that this is what the failing of the modern-day Eden is about: Ewa does not ask herself what she’s actually doing and why; instead of growing plants in an ordinary fashion, she chooses to build a laboratory-torture chamber and torment them there. That thought stayed with me when I was working with Krzyś Tyszkiewicz on the whole set design.” See: Marecki and Kletowski, <em>Królikiewicz</em>, 314.</p>
